cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE

The paper is about a shared task on word sense induction for the Russian language, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The task also involves clustering and classification of contexts, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of sense embeddings, which is a popular technique in the field of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper also mentions the use of deep neural networks, which is a common technique in the field of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
